        "mainbody": "'''Pilos Lafrett''' was a [[fish]]er and inventor who worked in the docks of the [[Baldur's Gate/Lower City|Lower City]] of [[Baldur's Gate]] in the late 15{{th}} century [[DR]].",
        "History": "In the {{YearlinkName|1492}}, Pilos invented a device that used pulleys and balanced weights that would do the fishing for him, while Pilos could nap. He informed his boss, [[Tohil]], of the invention and that it would be producing labor-free [[halibut]], but asked him not to touch the invention, while cockily also asking for a raise."
